SPADE
NEWSROOM

Newsroom integration can be messy and confusing, often resulting in vague structures of accountability and communication, inadequate or inefficient allocation of resources, friction between old-school roles and new-age processes, and consolidation only of real estate but not technology, manpower, audiences, data, et cetera.

SPADE a blueprint for modular workflow in omnimedia newsrooms is our attempt to solve misintegration.

Read more

It works as a single content supply chain with data-driven, multi-screen sourcing, production, assembling, distribution feeding all your news brands, across editions and languages, whatever the medium. Distinct news products instead operate as one platform, with print, broadcast and/or digital touchpoints.

It also works as a near-holocratic organisation structure that can adapt to the space, size and scale of any newsroom. Instead of building teams, hierarchies and silos around skills, it organises diverse skillsets journalism, research, technology, design around shared deliverables, with opportunities for lateral growth as a deterrent to attrition and burnout. For efficient and effective decision-making, the number of reports to a manager remains four or less across levels.
